                     /note="Tobacco Etch Virus (TEV) NIa protease recognition
                     site, engineered form ENLYFQG
                     (Glu-Asn-Leu-Tyr-Phe-Gln-Gly). TEV protease cleaves the
                     scissile peptide bond between the P1 Gln and the P1'
                     residue, i.e. after the Q (ENLYFQ|G), leaving a single
                     non-native Gly on the released downstream product.
                     Whole-part feature spanning all 7 residues; this is a
                     single atomic functional element with no functional
                     sub-features. P1'=Gly is an engineered variant of the
                     natural NIb|CP junction sequence ENLYFQS (P1'=Ser)."
